{
  "stem": "5103.4",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they said, it doesn't matter, doesn't matter, if you're sick, you're sick, you'll be all right, but you shouldn't have eaten so much.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I stuffed it down.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I was stuffing it down.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the very sad part of this was that my mother, who had waited for this so much, who had always said to me and to my father, we'll make it, we'll make it, wasn't there.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "She was nowhere there to share that, to share that emotion of, you know, we are free.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And it was a very sad thing, really, because I didn't know whether she was going to come out of the hospital.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They did-- they had diagnosed tuberculosis, is that she was malnutritioned.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And it was a freedom that was sort of, for a moment, very sad.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I kept on saying, I want my mother, I want mother to share this.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But we had to wait.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We couldn't start running on the road, because there were still people out that would have shot.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "There were still people, [INAUDIBLE], that were people that were collaborators, Dutch nationals that were collaborators with the Germans, that would have just shot.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Because now came the time that they were running scared, and they were now the frightened ones, and they would have just killed anybody in their path.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "So we had to wait.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And eventually, I remember, a few weeks later-- we waited with this Jan and Mien Baay, and it was tremendous.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "When my mother came home, she was-- had to have special-- she had special coupons for milk, and for all this for herself, because she had to have nourishment.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "So many eggs, so many-- I mean, it was amazing.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
